cs.AR, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the optimization of recurrent neural network (RNN) applications, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) workloads. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of a spatial accelerator, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The optimization strategy proposed in the paper involves loop constructs, which could fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates its implementation using DeepBench, which is a benchmark suite for neural network operations, and therefore could also fall under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
